    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You target a creature you can see within range, putting its physical form through the devastation of rapid aging. The target must make a Constitution saving throw, taking [[/r 12d12]] necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If the save fails, the target also ages to the point where it has only 30 days left before it dies of old age. In this aged state, whenever the target rolls an attack rolls, ability checks, or saving throws they roll 3 d20s and take the lowest result, and its walking speed is halved. Only the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.wVzKkFK2xss5ZzYC]{Wish} spell or the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplGreaterRes]{Greater Restoration} spell cast with a 9th-level spell slot can end these effects and restore the target to its previous age.</p>",
